<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1916-03-24T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1916-03-24T17:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.156/226</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Gonzales</persName>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-03-24T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 24, 1916, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Your March 22, 1 p.m. Department is unofficially advised that the
                            commission to study Cuban Ports matter has three months in which to
                            report. Cable briefly your opinion as to the present status of this
                            matter, both political and otherwise and whether this apparently
                            dilatory procedure may be expected to achieve results.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>